2 SENATE BILL 85
1 Preamble
2 WHEREAS, The U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs estimates that there are
3 approximately 130,000 blind veterans in the United States who are legally blind, and more
4 than one million who have low vision that causes a loss of ability to perform necessary daily
5 activities; and
6 WHEREAS, The American braille tactile flag was created by the Kansas Braille
7 Transcription Institute in Wichita, Kansas, and through the American Braille Flag Project,
8 to allow blind Americans and blind veterans to experience the American flag; and
9 WHEREAS, Maryland has five State veterans’ cemeteries visited by thousands of
10 people annually; and
11 WHEREAS, The State of Maryland is known as a state that recognizes the great
12 contributions of our blind community and honors the dedication of our uniformed services
13 members and veterans; now, therefore,
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – State Government
17 9–906.
18 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
19 (2) “AMERICAN BRAILLE TACTILE FLAG” MEANS A TACTILE FLAG
20 DESIGNED TO ALLOW BLIND PEOPLE TO EXPERIENCE THE AMERICAN FLAG,
21 INCLUDING A FLAG CREATED BY THE KANSAS BRAILLE TRANSCRIPTION INSTITUTE.
22 (3) “Eligible dependent” means:
23 (i) a child who meets the requirements stated in 38 C.F.R. §
24 38.620(e); or
25 (ii) a parent who meets the requirements stated in 38 C.F.R. §
26 38.620(i).
27 [(3)] (4) “Eligible spouse” means a spouse who meets the requirements
28 stated in 38 C.F.R. § 38.620(e).
29 [(4)] (5) “State veterans’ cemetery” means a cemetery that the
30 Department establishes under this section.

SENATE BILL 85 3
1 [(5)] (6) In this section and in § 9–907 of this subtitle, “veteran” means
2 an individual who:
3 (i) served other than dishonorably on active duty in the armed
4 forces of the United States; or
5 (ii) served other than dishonorably as a member of the State militia
6 ordered into active service of the United States by order of the President and was killed in
7 the line of duty.
8 [(6)] (7) “Washington Cemetery” means the Civil War cemetery grounds
9 authorized by Chapter 213 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 1870.
10 (b) The Department may establish one or more cemeteries in the State for the
11 burial of veterans and their eligible spouse or dependents as authorized by the Secretary.
12 (J) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DESIGNATE A LOCATION FOR AN AMERICAN
13 BRAILLE TACTILE FLAG TO BE PLACED IN ONE OR MORE STATE VETERANS’
14 CEMETERIES AS AUTHORIZED BY THE SECRETARY TO HONOR MEMBERS OF THE
15 UNIFORMED SERVICES, VETERANS, AND OTHER INDIVIDUALS IN THE STATE WHO
16 ARE BLIND OR VISUALLY IMPAIRED.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
18 October 1, 2025.
